gly interspersed in the old text. A facing English translation at last makes this text accessible to the Greek-less reader. The commentary explains Porphyry’s arguments and the editor’s textual decisions. The editor sheds new light on Porphyry’s use of the dictum that “the poet explains himself”, by differentiating it from that of Alexandria textual critics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aGriechenland /Philosophie. 4aHomer. 4aNeuplatonismus. 4aPorphyrios. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aGreece /Philosophy.  aHomer.  aNeo-Platonism.  aPorphyrios.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Classics and Near East Studies 2000-2014 (EN)z978311062109908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Classics and Near East Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110636178oZDB-23-GCN08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2010z9783110233544oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2010z978311023355108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET ALTERTUM 2010z9783110233575oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311019543940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311021680640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110216806423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110216806/original  a978-3-11-023355-1  E-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2010b2010  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  a978-3-11-062109-9  DGBA Backlist Classics and Near East Studies 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_